adjectives.description: fleshy (comparative fleshier or more fleshy, superlative fleshiest or most fleshy)

entries.meaning: Of, related to, or resembling flesh.
(of a person) Having considerable flesh; plump.
examples: He was a large fleshy man, weighing at least two hundred pounds, and he quickly became a faithful representation of a quivering jelly-mountain of fat.
